\subsection{When to Use This}{

Use pairwise Wilcoxon when:
\itemize{
\item Your Friedman test shows significant differences (p < 0.05)
\item You want to know which specific measurements differ
\item Your data are ordinal or violate normality assumptions
\item You have repeated measures or matched groups
